
SELECT TOP 1000 [TemplateID]
      ,[ResultName]
      ,[ResultInfoKey]
      ,[ResultInfoValue]
  FROM [QutSensors].[dbo].[Processor_TemplateResult]

TemplateID	ResultName	ResultInfoKey	ResultInfoValue
1	LLR_VALUE	COMMENT_ABOUT_LLR	The log likelihood ratio, in this case, is interpreted as follows. Let v1 be the test vocalisation and let v2 be an 'average' vocalisation used to train the Markov Model. Let p1 = p(v1 | MM) and let p2 = p(v2 | MM). Then LLR = log (p1 /p2).  Note 1: In theory LLR takes only negative values because p1 < p2. Note 2: For same reason, LLR's max value = 0.0 (i.e. test str has same prob has training sample. Note 3: In practice, LLR can have positive value when p1 > p2 because p2 is an average.
1	LLR_VALUE	COMMENT_ABOUT_THRESHOLD	The null hypothesis is that the test sequence is a true positive. Accept null hypothesis if LLR >= -6.64.  Reject null hypothesis if LLR <  -6.64.
1	LLR_VALUE	THRESHOLD	-6.64
1	LLR_VALUE	UNITS	LLR
1	TIME_OF_TOP_SCORE	COMMENT	Time from beginning of recording.
1	TIME_OF_TOP_SCORE	UNITS	seconds
1	VOCAL_COUNT	COMMENT	The number of vocalisations that contained at least one recognised syllable.
